CSCI 551 — Assignment 4 (submission layout)

Directories
- hello_cuda/          CUDA hello + deviceQuery (cscigpu)
- cuda-integrators/    cuda_trap1 + trap_seq (cscigpu)
- functiongen/         timeinterp CSV, ex4.h table
- compare/             MPI example (ex4.h LUT integration pattern)
- train_ex4/           Exercise 4 train simulation (MPI + numerical Euler); build on ECC

Quick commands

cscigpu (CUDA_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-12.9 typical):
  cd hello_cuda && make && ./cuda_hello 64 && ./cuda_hello1 8 128 && ./deviceQuery
  cd ../cuda-integrators && make CUDA_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-12.9
  ./trap_seq 1000000 0 3.14159265358979323846 && ./cuda_trap1 1000000
  cd ../functiongen && make timeinterp && ./timeinterp 10 | tail -n +5 > Ex4-Acceleration-interp-10Hz.csv

ECC cluster (MPI for train_ex4):
  cd train_ex4 && make
  mpirun -np 1 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.001
  mpirun -np 1 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001
  mpirun -np 2 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001
  mpirun -np 4 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001
  mpirun -np 8 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001
  mpirun -np 16 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001

Submit: separate written report (PDF) plus ZIP of code, Makefiles, sample logs — per Canvas instructions.
